    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "version_discovery_bool_ignored",
      "summary": "Startup treats version discovery as successful on any channel receive, even explicit failure signals.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/startup_orchestrator.go",
        "goseg/config/version.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`startVersionDiscovery` sends `versionUpdate` from `config.SyncVersionInfo()` into `versionUpdateChannel`.",
        "`waitForVersionDiscovery` uses `case <-versionUpdate:` and unconditionally logs \"Version info retrieved\"; it does not read/use the bool.",
        "`SyncVersionInfo` returns `false` on fetch/persist failures, so startup can report success and skip fallback despite failed discovery."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Change `waitForVersionDiscovery` to read the bool (`ok := <-versionUpdate`) and treat `false` as failure: log a failure message, load local version fallback, and optionally return/propagate an error so startup health reflects degraded state.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "background_failure_signal_loss"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "background_service_error_contract_mismatch",
      "summary": "Background services use incompatible failure contracts, causing updater failures to be logged-and-dropped while peers fail fast.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/routines/version.go",
        "goseg/startup_orchestrator.go",
        "goseg/routines/logstream/logs.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`superviseBackgroundService` expects service functions to return errors for health/reporting.",
        "In `routines/version.go`, `callUpdater`/`updateBinary` handle many operational failures by logging and `return` (void), so `CheckVersionLoopWithContext` typically never returns these failures.",
        "By contrast, `OldLogsCleanerWithContext` escalates repeated failures by returning an error after threshold, so supervised behavior differs materially across services."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Standardize background loop contracts: return structured errors from updater paths (or an error channel) and let the supervisor decide retry/backoff/escalation. Keep logging, but do not make logging the terminal error sink for recoverable/retriable operational failures.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "background_failure_signal_loss"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "websocket_write_failures_silently_demoted",
      "summary": "WebSocket write failures in session broadcast are downgraded to state flips without error context or consistent cleanup.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/session/ws.go",
        "goseg/routines/logstream/logs.go",
        "goseg/leak/handler.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`BroadcastAuth`/`BroadcastUnauth` call `client.Write`, then only set `client.Active = false` on error and continue; no log, close, or explicit removal path is triggered there.",
        "`SysLogStreamerWithContext` handles write errors with explicit log + `conn.Close()` + removal scheduling, preserving failure context and cleanup intent.",
        "Leak path (`reportLeakError`) logs queueing failures, showing another different write-failure policy for socket/channel boundaries."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a shared connection-write error policy for websocket boundaries: always attach context (client/token/channel), close the connection, schedule removal, and emit one structured error signal/log path.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "inconsistent_io_boundary_policy"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Failure signaling is not treated as a first-class contract across long-running services; bools/logs are mixed with returned errors.",
